defaultDavid Bancroft – Written evidencedefault&#xa0;
defaultI am a member of 2 rambling clubs and walk every Sunday in any one of 5 national parks accessible from Manchester on day trips.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhen I encounter much mud and water in deep ruts and tranches created by motorbikes and 4x4 vehicles I think something must be done to stop irreparable damage.  Surely National Parks are not intended to accommodate convoys of 4x4s and motorbikes.
default&#xa0;
defaultMy purpose in writing this letter is to support formal submissions made by:-
default1. YDGLA (Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance)
default2. PDGLA (Peak District Green Lanes Alliance)
default3. GLEAM (Green Lanes Environmental Action Group)
default4. GLPG (Green Lanes Protection Group)
default&#xa0;
defaultPlease give their submissions your favourable consideration.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
